news.title: Surat: User charges hiked, no tax increase
news.para: Of the 1.54 lakh streetlights, 1.28 lakh have already been converted to LED while the remaining 26,605 will be converted this year.

news.title: In Dehradun, online property tax payment surpasses offline mode
news.para: The tax department of the Dehradun Municipal Corporation (DMC) has, so far, collected Rs 24 crore in property tax for this financial year. In contrast, the civic body had collected about Rs 17 crore in property tax till January 26 date last year.

news.title: Nashik civic body slaps warrants to over 400 property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has given the tax defaulters a deadline of 21 days for paying the dues or they would face the action of confiscation of their properties. These defaulters have pending property tax dues for the past few years.

news.title: In just 10 days, Hyderabad development body razes 78 illegal buildings
news.para: Cracking the whip on unauthorised constructions in its jurisdiction, the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) has demolished 78 buildings and sealed another 23 structures in the past 10 days.

news.title: Ahmedabad: No building-use nod, 16 illegal constructions razed
news.para: The residential units from which illegal constructions were demolished were located in three societies in Lambha and one in Jamalpur. Eight of the commercial units were located in TP scheme 125 in Lambha and one was in Rakhial.

news.title: North Delhi civic body to transfer eight land pockets to DMRC
news.para: All eight pockets belong to the horticulture department of the north corporation and of them, five will be utilised for constructing the entry and exit of the MRTS stations or their buildings.

news.title: No registration of property on water bodies: Madras HC
news.para: It shall be ensured by the authority granting approval for the lay-out or building construction or assessment of property tax or electricity or water connection that the relevant property has not been notified as water body in the list published in the official website

news.title: Rajkot civic body waives off property tax for theatres, hotels
news.para: The standing committee also approved the work of laying water pipelines in the newly merged area of the city and construction of a waste processing plant.

news.title: CIDCO launches mass housing scheme in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Maharashtra Urban Development Minister Eknath Shinde said the CIDCO housing scheme was gaining popularity due to its quality construction, affordable rates and transparent online processing.

news.title: Builders requests Telangana government to reconsider hike in property registration charges
news.para: Telangana government is mulling hiking registration charges – by 20% to 50% depending on the nature of the property – beginning next month. Earlier in July 2021, the state had revised the registration costs apart from increasing the stamp duty from 6% to 7.5%.

news.title: Builders request Maharashtra government not to raise RR rates, expect boosters
news.para: The property registration department has started discussions on the division-wise revision of the Ready Reckoner (RR) rates, which are announced in April every year. There was no revision in the rates due to the pandemic last year. Tthere was a slight increase (1.74%) in the rates announced in September 2020.

news.title: UP-RERA fines seven builders over Rs 1 crore for not handing over flats within deadline
news.para: All the seven builders have failed to deliver the units to their buyers within the stipulated deadlines. While four have projects in Noida, two are from Ghaziabad and one is based in Meerut.

news.title: Home First Finance posts net profit of Rs 46 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income during October-December 2021 rose over 37 per cent to Rs 152 crore from Rs 110 crore, while the asset under management (AUM) has crossed Rs 5,000 crore in January 2022, it added.

news.title: HSIL's profit down 21% to Rs 29 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: HSIL's revenue from operation was higher at Rs 638.75 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 541.48 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's profit up 6% to Rs 767.33 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: "Even the provisions were less in the quarter because of the provisions we had made earlier," LIC Housing's Managing Director and CEO Y Viswanatha Gowd said.
